```python
import csv

presidents = [("Washington", "27", "1789", "4"), ("Adams", "65", "1797", "8"), ("Jefferson", "69", "1801", "4"), ("Madison", "75", "1809", "4"), ("Monroe", "72", "1809", "4")]

with open('presidents.csv', 'w') as csvfile:
    writer = csv.writer(csvfile)
    writer.writerow(['Name', 'Age when Started Office', 'Year Started', 'Number of Years Served'])
    for row in presidents:
        writer.writerow(row)
```
